 <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Live your life so the preacher won't have to lie at your funeral.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mamagadfly>MamaGadfly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 316<br> <font color=#3333ff>(4/2/03 5:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=172.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   re: collections</span><hr size=1> Was in collections with several credit card and mortgage companies and can respond here...<br>
<br>
&quot;They start daily collection calls the 1st day after the payment is due and even if you tell them that you have already sent it or when you will be sending the payment,&quot;<br>
<br>
Which they have a right to do (one can debate how this affects customer relations). All banks have levels of accounts though and if you were &quot;highly valued&quot; and had lots of money with them in other investments and a platinum you would NOT be called this quickly. Depends on past payment history and credit rating (internal and Fair Isaac) too.<br>
<br>
&quot;thay harrass you every day until they get and post the payment (which takes up to 10 days after they actually get it) Their so called customer service is non existent&quot;<br>
<br>
Firstly, this is not intended to be customer service...that's another dept, it's collections to whom you are talking. They all use predictive dialers, but it is highly irregular to be called daily so you are either exaggerating, the collector in question cannot use the system correctly, or they need to adjust the dialer...could be a combo of all 3. Notation alone doesn't stop calls, one must set out the next &quot;workdate&quot;.<br>
<br>
Harass is also a relative term and perhaps the collector is being rude. Though the FDCPA does not directly relate to you since Citifinancial is collecting on their own debt rather than 3rd party, (unless this is charged off or transferred debt), you do have optoins. They cannot make false claimes, threaten illegal action, prison etc. or call more than once a day. <br>
<br>
E-mail me privately if you want more info, but I've collected and trained collectors at all levels so I know a bit about this. I sympathize if this is your first EVER late payment, but suspect perhaps it is not and your account may then be flagged. <br>
<br>
If this is not the case, you should call the collectins department to complain and may even fax a letter requestion NO MORE calls.If they make even one more after that they have violated federal law and you have them by the balls. Not many people know this and NO collector would ever volunteer it. Will solve your problem permanently.<br>
<br>
ST <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mormongirl2>Mormongirl2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#3333ff>(4/3/03 1:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=172.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re: collections</span><hr size=1> I am not exaggerating.  and there have been times when they have called 3 times in one day, which I know is illegal and I have told them this and hung up on them.  In discussing this with a neighbor, they have the same thing with Citifinancial.  Without going into any personal financial details, lets just say with my sons medical problems we have about 10 medical bills we pay each month, so there are months when we do not make the due date.  My husband works on comission and he works for a small company that pays commissions anywhere between the 10th and the 20th (basically whenever they get around to it) So that affects the time the payment is sent as well.  But they get their money and have for over 5 years, which makes me all the more annoyed.  <br>
